The Asterisk Pattern Printer generates a right-angled triangle pattern of asterisks (*). The pattern consists of:
n rows, where n is the input parameter
Each row contains i asterisks, where i is the current row number (1-indexed)
The pattern grows by one asterisk per row

PATTERN:

*
**
***
****
*****

PROGRAMM:

class HelloWorld {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int n = 5;
        for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
            for (int j = 1; j <= i; j++) {
                System.out.print("*");
            }
            System.out.println();
        }
    }
}
